CSS Syntax
-CSS rule consists of selector and declaraton block

CSS Syntax

Selector Declaration
h1 {
  color: blue; 
  font-size: 12px;
}

h1 -> selector
color -> property
blue; -> value

selector -> points to HTML element you want style
declaration block -> contains 1 or more declarations separated by semicolons
each declaration includes CSS property name and value, seperated by colon
multiple CSS declarations seperated by semicolons and declaration blocks are surrounded by curly braces


ex.
p {
  color: red;
  text-align: center;
}

explained:
p -> selector in CSS (points to HTML element you want to style <p>)
color -> property and red is property value
text-align -> property and center is property value


